I made this as the squash dish for a big Thanksgiving dinner (serving 12). Of all the recipes I was attempting, this was the one I was most skeptical about. I LOVE butternut squash and I make it quite often --- just with butter, maple syrup, salt and pepper. I wasn't sure how goat cheese was going to mesh with the flavor of the squash... I was pleasantly surprised! It was really good. The flavor of the leeks was just great. I didn't have any hazelnuts so I had to use walnuts --- it was good, but I'm sure it would have been better with hazelnuts. I make it a bit less chuncky than the picture suggests, and it was still a bit too chucky for me. When I make it again, I will half- mash the squash. I like my flavors infused a bit more. I recommend this recipe!

Rating: 4
This was the star of our dinner. Next time I would cut the cream or lighten it, use more sage and maybe cut the squash in smaller dice.

