Rating: 4
This was to die for! I confess, I used the heavy cream called for in the recipe. Why fight it? It's the holiday season. (I did use cooking spray instead of the additional T. of butter to grease the pan). I actually had goat cheese, whipping cream and butternut squash on hand and it seemed like Fate that I make this recipe. My husband and I both loved it. The sweetness of the squash and sauteed leeks, the slight sourness of the goat cheese and the crunch of the hazelnuts complemented each other perfectly. This would be great for Thanksgiving, particularly an all-adult one. I have a feeling kids would look upon it with a jaundiced eye.

